# Awesome CSS Curation Guide

This rule orchestrates the curation process for the Awesome CSS repository. To avoid duplication, the core taxonomy, formatting, and curation constraints are maintained in the project's official documentation.

## Core Conventions

**You MUST read and strictly follow the rules defined in `docs/conventions.md` before curating any links.**

The `docs/conventions.md` file is the single source of truth for:
- Taxonomy and target sections
- Allowed type tags
- Mandatory link formatting
- Curation constraints (e.g., keeping content organized by problem solved, never removing existing links)

## Additional AI-Specific Constraints

- All added content (descriptions, titles, categories) MUST be in English.

## Delegation

- Validation details are defined in `.cursor/rules/curation-validation.mdc`.
- Skill execution details are defined in `.cursor/skills/curator/SKILL.md`.
